Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.08,0:01:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year After Colony 175...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.58,0:01:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,...the leader of the colonies\Nwas assassinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.29,0:01:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Five Gundams were sent\Nto Earth to take revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.16,0:01:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, since OZ's activities\Nin space...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.26,0:01:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,...took the form of cooperation\Nrather than control...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.80,0:01:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...the colonies decided\Nto accept OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.87,0:01:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The year After Colony 195.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.34,0:01:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As OZ moves to take over\Nboth Earth and outer space...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.84,0:01:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...Gundams are labeled rebels\Nand are isolated from society.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.31,0:02:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,With no place to return...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.35,0:02:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,...the Gundams and\Ntheir pilots...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,...must fight for a reason to\Nexist in the changing world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.59,0:02:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an astro suit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.63,0:02:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The astro suit has also\Nbeen set as a target!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.63,0:02:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Cancel it! Hurry!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.50,0:02:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll eliminate all obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.12,0:02:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say the lunar base?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.29,0:02:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.45,0:02:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A large amount of\NGundanium alloy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.06,0:02:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...is being brought into\Nthe Lunar Base factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.33,0:02:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably for making\Na new type of mobile suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.06,0:02:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are your plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.90,0:02:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.50,0:02:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- You'll get in the way.\N- What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.84,0:03:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna need time to recover,\Nconsidering all that's happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.68,0:03:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But how about being a little\Nkinder to me once in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.31,0:03:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not go to school\Ninstead of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.88,0:03:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already got the admission\Ntaken care of, under your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.75,0:03:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.59,0:03:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, your name would\Nstick out here, but still!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.09,0:03:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of complaining,\Njust rest and get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.57,0:03:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't overdo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Like he's gonna listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.17,0:03:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course he'll overdo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.81,0:03:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll decide once I get\Nto the moon...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.77,0:03:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,...whether to steal the new\Nmobile suit or destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.68,0:03:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With only one sixth the\Ngravity of Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.92,0:03:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...the moon wasn't suitable\Nfor human inhabitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.42,0:03:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon completion of\Nthe Space Colonies...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.09,0:03:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...construction was started\Non lunar research facilities...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.30,0:03:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...and major factories of\Nvarious sorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.83,0:03:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The moon further developed...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.57,0:04:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...into a popular tourist\Ndestination for Earthlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.07,0:04:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It prospered until its\Nsuppression by the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.78,0:04:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,After OZ dismantled\Nthe Alliance Military...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.25,0:04:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,...the moon was again allowed\Nto be a tourist destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.28,0:04:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,People saw it as a sign that\Npeace was returning to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.22,0:04:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,People are now free to travel\Nbetween the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that OZ has already\Nseized much of outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.26,0:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been handing out\Na lot of gifts these days...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.43,0:04:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...to try and win people over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.04,0:04:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Once people trust OZ,\Nthe rest is easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.27,0:04:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Resources and labor will\Nsoon all be controlled by OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.38,0:04:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's build OZ a real rascal\Nto keep them occupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.19,0:04:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mercurius defense system...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.26,0:04:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,...is looking pretty impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.89,0:04:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Vayeate should\Nstart taking shape...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:05:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,...once the mainframe is built.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.00,0:05:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a matter of time\Nbefore it's completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.47,0:05:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't intend to work\Nunder OZ forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.17,0:05:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Officially speaking, this is\NLady Une's project.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.01,0:05:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But they'll be selecting\Nmobile suit pilots...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.07,0:05:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...from among the\Ncolony citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.91,0:05:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This could all become\Nquite interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.71,0:05:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt if things will\Nwork out that well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.78,0:05:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero won't bother with\Nthe selection process.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.29,0:05:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more his style to go\Nstraight for their throats.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case we'll complete\Nthe powerful mobile suits...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.83,0:05:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...that OZ wants so badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.76,0:05:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Then prove that OZ can be\Ndestroyed by its own weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.77,0:05:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is OZ really thinking to\Nestablish a nation in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.78,0:05:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we're free from\Nthe Alliance's control...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.31,0:05:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,...civilians can communicate\Nbetween the colonies...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.65,0:05:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...and with the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.02,0:05:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We have OZ to thank for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.42,0:06:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't see why they must\Ntry to control our future.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.69,0:06:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, but given the present\Nsize of the Space Colonies...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.36,0:06:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...it'd be strange for us not\Nto consider becoming a nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, but this is\Nour problem here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.73,0:06:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It says our main industries\Nwill be military technology...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.24,0:06:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,...and mobile suit production.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.67,0:06:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.57,0:06:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The colony delegates are having\Nproblems with that document.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.81,0:06:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That seems natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.65,0:06:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They've seen the Alliance's\Nreckless use of arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.72,0:06:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,To them, a mobile suit\Nmanufacturer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.72,0:06:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...is like a merchant of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.06,0:06:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The nations supporting OZ\Nlike space technology...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.69,0:06:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...only because they can use it\Nto improve military power.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.60,0:06:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see the peace-minded\Ncolonies going along with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.43,0:06:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They can think of our plan\Nfor the arms as a deterrent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.54,0:06:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrangements will be made\Nto bring what space is lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.38,0:06:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What space is lacking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.98,0:06:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Proper public order.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.58,0:07:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you all waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you had a chance to read\Nthrough our document?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.76,0:07:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe one of the reasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...the Space Colonies were\Nconsidered a threat to Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,...was that the colonies lacked\Nan organizational structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.70,0:07:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I think forming a nation is\Na step in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.57,0:07:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're having problems\Nwith the major industries?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.47,0:07:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.77,0:07:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How can there be world peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.77,0:07:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,...based on this idea that arms\Nare needed as a deterrent?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.08,0:07:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,History's taught us otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.85,0:07:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We can establish a new public\Norder different from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.82,0:07:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're proud this technology will\Nbe the source of our capital...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.22,0:07:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...but we shouldn't be\Nconsidering military power!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.29,0:07:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In my heart, I feel this war\Nhas already come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.90,0:07:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ is a military organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.97,0:07:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We've made an effort to settle\Nrepeated disputes on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.74,0:07:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal of the United\NEarth Sphere Alliance...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...was to achieve peace without\Nrelying on military power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.38,0:08:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you're suggesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.51,0:08:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But think what those\Nstrategies gave rise to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.61,0:08:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need for\Nreckless battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't discuss\Nmankind's beauty...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.22,0:08:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,...without acknowledging\Nthe desire to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.79,0:08:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I the only one who\Nadmires man's will to fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.71,0:08:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I hadn't expected OZ to\Nrestore it to this extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.91,0:08:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't hand this\NGundam over to OZ!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.22,0:08:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.65,0:08:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.49,0:08:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be some kind\Nof expert...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.96,0:08:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...to sneak in here at night\Nand set explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.29,0:08:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hand me that detonation switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.30,0:08:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.17,0:08:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not getting that Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.57,0:09:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.84,0:09:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All those explosives and they\Ndidn't even make a dent!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.58,0:09:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's disappointing, but\Nthe Gundam's sure impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.48,0:09:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn! She's pretty aggressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.22,0:09:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ has found us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.89,0:09:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get outta here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.16,0:09:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We've gotta be at least\Nas brave as that lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We must recover Master Quatre's\NGundam at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.33,0:09:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Leo troops, get a move on!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.06,0:09:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The enemy's in the hangar{\i0}\N{\i1}with the Gundam Zero Four!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.64,0:09:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.08,0:09:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We barely managed to sneak in\Nand now look what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.68,0:09:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Abdul's plans never work out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.19,0:09:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?!\NDid you say something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.69,0:09:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in a hurry, so get Master\NQuatre's Gundam here pronto!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.20,0:10:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What's taking you, Auda?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.20,0:10:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't fight so close to me!!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.34,0:10:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It wasn't easy swiping{\i0}\N{\i1}this carrier!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.81,0:10:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't blame me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.61,0:10:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We were supposed to wait\Nuntil OZ rebuilt the Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.94,0:10:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't expect things would\Nget moving this quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.08,0:10:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hurry up, Ahmad!!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.52,0:10:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.17,0:10:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.00,0:10:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it! Perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.90,0:10:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mission accomplished!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.07,0:10:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.78,0:10:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.85,0:10:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why'd you stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.95,0:10:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't even think about fighting!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.95,0:11:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that bloody woman again!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.92,0:11:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's Auda!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.32,0:11:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think we're enemies!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.49,0:11:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I sensed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But the guy I know would\Ntry to destroy the Gundam.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy I know would be\Nsad if it were destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.44,0:11:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're hoping to restore it\Nto make him happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.97,0:11:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Does she know a Gundam\Npilot as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.51,0:11:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We belong to the Maganac\NCorps of the Middle East.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.45,0:11:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave this Gundam\Nin our hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.42,0:11:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a great kid,\Nthis pilot of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.69,0:11:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So does your pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.80,0:11:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd better go and\Npick up...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.90,0:11:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...what the other great\Nkid left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.86,0:12:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The following footage is{\i0}\N{\i1}of an event held today...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.63,0:12:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...that is very significant{\i0}\N{\i1}for the colonies' defense.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.20,0:12:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These young volunteers{\i0}\N{\i1}are vying for a position...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.47,0:12:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...to fight for the safety{\i0}\N{\i1}of the colonies.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.94,0:12:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is everyone going along\Nwith OZ's every word?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.81,0:12:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The youngsters fared well...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.88,0:12:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...in a firing test designed{\i0}\N{\i1}to reflect a real battle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.15,0:12:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the next test, obstacles\Nrepresenting enemies...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.45,0:12:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,...will be placed along each\Nmobile suit's path.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.52,0:12:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The bombs are imitations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.26,0:12:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But they carry an impact.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Be careful!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.79,0:12:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes, sir!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.73,0:12:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they come!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.90,0:12:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Commence attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.84,0:12:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.28,0:12:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're just amateurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.26,0:13:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe that guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.73,0:13:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.13,0:13:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is test pilot 1.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.73,0:13:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm finished with the test.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.34,0:13:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Test pilot 1, confirm your name!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.81,0:13:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Trowa Barton.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.47,0:13:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Colonel, Trowa Barton{\i0}\N{\i1}is extraordinary!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.61,0:13:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even though he's been{\i0}\N{\i1}through some simulations...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.01,0:13:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...he couldn't make such{\i0}\N{\i1}maneuvers in his first battle!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.35,0:13:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.95,0:13:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He must've had some{\i0}\N{\i1}previous training.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.39,0:13:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At an extremely high level, too!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.39,0:13:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But his background has\Nbeen checked hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.26,0:13:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes, and there were no problems.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.50,0:13:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it sounds like he's got\Nsome natural talents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.07,0:13:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Talents that he never had\Nthe chance to use before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But isn't it possible that he's{\i0}\N{\i1}been sent to destroy OZ?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.97,0:13:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He might even be a Gundam pilot!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find out soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.21,0:13:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Trowa Barton.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.28,0:14:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One more test.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.61,0:14:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Completely destroy the{\i0}\N{\i1}next target!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.69,0:14:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.93,0:14:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's the matter, Trowa Barton?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.70,0:14:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fire at the target!!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.67,0:14:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Colonel!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.67,0:14:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He is a Gundam pilot,{\i0}\N{\i1}just as I figured!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.14,0:14:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll get rid of him!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.18,0:14:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Lend me that beam cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.85,0:14:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.38,0:14:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's made of Gundanium alloy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.72,0:14:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A Leo rifle won't do the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.06,0:14:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A Gundam, responsible for{\i0}\N{\i1}the misunderstandings...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.06,0:14:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...between Earth and the{\i0}\N{\i1}colonies...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.73,0:14:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and causing destruction...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.96,0:14:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...will be destroyed by a colony{\i0}\N{\i1}citizen wishing for peace.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.10,0:14:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ladies and gentlemen,{\i0}\N{\i1}stand by to witness this!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Deathscythe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.47,0:14:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up too easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.64,0:14:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be okay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.04,0:15:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll come out fine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.81,0:15:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,About to commence second test.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.73,0:15:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.43,0:15:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,NO!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.50,0:15:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa Barton's brain waves\Nand pulse remain unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.37,0:15:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he's the perfect pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.24,0:15:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But I still have some doubts\Nabout him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.04,0:15:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy's clearly willing\Nto cooperate with OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.28,0:15:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,People with talent are capable\Nof understanding us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.46,0:15:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Those sparkles...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.76,0:15:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're my tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.97,0:16:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The new type of mobile suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.98,0:16:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the parts are\Nstill being designed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.45,0:16:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.46,0:16:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Test pilot No. 1; Colonel Une{\i0}\N{\i1}wishes to speak with you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.70,0:16:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wait there!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.40,0:16:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.17,0:16:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Une!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still possible that\Nhe's a Gundam pilot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.31,0:16:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it'd be wiser\Nto meet him by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.74,0:16:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.78,0:16:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He's come to try and\Nunderstand OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.65,0:16:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be rude not to meet\Nwith him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.48,0:16:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we'll have a lot\Nto talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.05,0:16:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,As two individuals who\Nlove outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.12,0:16:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.36,0:16:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Nichol,\Nwhat are you so afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.89,0:17:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.76,0:17:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's put an end to\Nthe fighting, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.54,0:17:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Lady Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.11,0:17:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.24,0:17:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is Lady Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.68,0:17:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Commander of\NOZ's Space Operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.92,0:17:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've had experience\Nwith labor mobile suits...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...in your job repairing\Nthe colony's outer walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.55,0:17:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Your outstanding test\Nresults today...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.99,0:17:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,...have the OZ soldiers\Ncompletely baffled.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.23,0:17:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always felt I had what\Nit'd take to be a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.63,0:17:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I'm hired?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.80,0:17:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's work together to bring\Npeace to outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.93,0:17:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just hoping that my\Nabilities will come in handy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.00,0:17:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...to defeat the Alliance's\NSpace Forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.21,0:17:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never thought about\Npeace in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.41,0:17:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I thought of myself as\Nthe right type of person for OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.58,0:17:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The right type of person?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.32,0:17:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm impressed how OZ is\Ngradually taking over space...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.75,0:17:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...while appearing to act\Nout of friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.69,0:18:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,People may think of it\Nas foul play, but it suits me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.82,0:18:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking over?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, "foul play"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.99,0:18:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ is a place where the\Ncrafty are acknowledged.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.20,0:18:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it's about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.70,0:18:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.93,0:18:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.71,0:18:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.48,0:18:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.55,0:18:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs to get some rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.28,0:18:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.55,0:18:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.59,0:18:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.22,0:18:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You might have tricked\Nthe Colonel, but not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.99,0:18:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa Barton.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.12,0:18:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Colonel has ordered\Nyou...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.16,0:18:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...to come back in two hours\Nto test OZ's new mobile suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.33,0:18:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But just now the Colonel...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.20,0:18:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une is a much stronger\Nperson in her uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.47,0:18:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She might feel like killing\Nsomeone as questionable as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.88,0:19:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm Lady Une of OZ?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.62,0:19:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do I work under Treize?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.17,0:19:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't take you long\Nto find your pilots, did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.71,0:19:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,These five have been selected\Nfrom the colony citizens...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.98,0:19:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,...as prospective pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.31,0:19:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is Trowa Barton.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.48,0:19:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He's outstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.05,0:19:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He should be able\Nto control any suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.88,0:19:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,These mobile suits of ours\Nwon't be simple to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.49,0:19:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear they're better than\Nthe Gundams.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.69,0:19:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.82,0:19:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How far have you gotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.46,0:19:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mercurius is 80%\Ncomplete...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.83,0:19:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...and the Vayeate is about\N50% complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.17,0:19:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the reason for\Ndeveloping two models?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.33,0:19:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We designed these two\Nsuit models...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.14,0:19:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...as opposing principles in\Nbattle...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.81,0:20:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...that is, offense and defense\Nin their extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.61,0:20:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With the Vayeate, we added the\Nlargest possible beam cannon...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.91,0:20:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...without affecting mobility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.48,0:20:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And with the Mercurius\Nwe added a defense shield...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.42,0:20:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,...to withstand such a beam\Ncannon attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.05,0:20:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Which would win if they\Nwere to fight each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.06,0:20:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, the one with\Nthe better pilot would win.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.66,0:20:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you kidding?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.13,0:20:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So the race to determine the\Nsuperiority of mobile suits...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.03,0:20:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,...is meaningless, since\Ntheir value...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.77,0:20:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...is directly dependent on\Nthe abilities of the pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.00,0:20:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sharp; I see why\Nyou were selected by OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.04,0:20:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.27,0:20:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Silence Trowa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.08,0:20:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave him alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.14,0:20:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll be piloting one\Nof those suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.18,0:20:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll allow his questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.55,0:20:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, yes ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.48,0:20:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What tests will you be\Ndemonstrating for us today?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.32,0:20:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.25,0:20:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show you the defense\Nsystem of the Mercurius.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.86,0:20:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the latest system, which\Ncreates an electric field...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.96,0:20:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...to allow it to reflect any\Nbeam fired by the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.03,0:20:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Vayeate?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.56,0:20:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vayeate still needs\Nsome work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.93,0:21:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't even charged\Nwith energy yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.80,0:21:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.87,0:21:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vayeate's moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.51,0:21:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Activate the Mercurius shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.18,0:21:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.69,0:21:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.35,0:21:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you gonna make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.19,0:21:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.39,0:21:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What'd I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.76,0:22:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My weapon, he's something,\Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.33,0:22:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.73,0:22:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He even came after us!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.93,0:22:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's some weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.92,0:23:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A white mobile suit\Napproaches a colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.26,0:23:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it's determined to\Nbe Zechs' Tallgeese...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.26,0:23:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,...Lady Une orders Trowa\Nand Heero to attack it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.27,0:23:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The injured Quatre returns\Nto the Winner residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.37,0:23:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But, to his great sadness,\Nthere he finds his father...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.24,0:23:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...being solely blamed and\Ncriticized by the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.01,0:23:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on Gundam Wing, Episode 21,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.40,0:23:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"Grief Stricken Quatre".
